### New file: `backend/src/routes/org/org.billing.routes.ts`

**7 endpoints** under `/api/v1/org/:orgId/billing/`:

| Method | Path | Auth | Role | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|------|---------|
| `GET` | `/balance` | Yes | All org roles | Current balance, tier, totals, unlocked features |
| `GET` | `/transactions` | Yes | OWNER, ADMIN | Paginated transaction ledger (filter by `action`, `limit`, `offset`) |
| `POST` | `/purchase` | Yes | OWNER | Initiate token purchase (placeholder for Paddle/Stripe integration) |
| `POST` | `/confirm` | Yes | OWNER | Client-side payment confirmation with idempotency guard |
| `POST` | `/deduct` | Yes | OWNER, ADMIN | Deduct tokens for an action (returns 402 if insufficient) |
| `GET` | `/features` | Yes | All org roles | Features available for the org's current tier |
| `POST` | `/webhook` | No | — | Payment provider webhook (HMAC placeholder, idempotent) |

### Key design decisions:
- **Tier derived from `totalPurchased`** — spending doesn't downgrade, bonuses don't upgrade
- **Idempotent payment processing** — `ProcessedOrgTransaction` unique constraint prevents double-crediting across client confirm + webhook paths
- **Atomic balance mutations** — all token changes use `prisma.$transaction`
- **Tier thresholds**: STARTER (0), PRO (250), ENTERPRISE (500)

### Fixes included:
- **Org router was imported but never mounted** in `routes/index.ts` — added `router.use('/org', orgRouter)`
